    {% call components.section("Usage") -%}

        <p>Progress steps are best used when displaying content that must be completed in a particular order.</p>
        <h4>Mobile</h4>
        <p>If a task has fewer steps and short text labels, the horizontal orientation can be used on mobile. Otherwise, if a task has more steps and longer text labels, the vertical orientation should be used instead.</p>

        <img src="{{ '/assets/progress-steps/alert-mobile-usage.svg' | url }}" alt="Mobile usage alert">

        <br /> <br />

        {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/progress-steps/progress-steps-mobile-usage.svg' | url }}" alt="Progress steps component mobile usage" style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">
        {%- endcall %}

        <h4>Progression</h4>
        <p>Steps are organized from left to right or top to bottom to demonstrate a user completing a task by moving through a linear multi-step process. A user should be able to return to any previously completed step to review data that will be submitted when they finish.</p>

        <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
        {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/progress-steps/progress-steps-progression-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Progress steps component progression, part 1" style="--inline-img-max-width: 691px;">
        {%- endcall %}
        </div>

        <p class="footnote" style="margin-top:-3rem; letter-spacing: 0.2px;">When completing a task normally, a user would move from left to right or top to bottom</p>

        <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
        {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/progress-steps/progress-steps-progression-2.svg' | url }}" alt="Progress steps component progression, part 2" style="--inline-img-max-width: 687px;">
        {%- endcall %}
        </div>

        <p class="footnote" style="margin-top:-3rem; letter-spacing: 0.2px;">If a user needs to return to a previously completed step, they should be able to unless the task is complete</p>

        <h4>Validation</h4>

        <p>Validation is a state that displays if a previous step has been completed or if there is an error that needs to be resolved first before a user can proceed. If a user attempts to continue to another step without resolving the issue or inputting the required data, an <a href="https://ux.redhat.com/components/alert/" target="_blank">Alert</a> is displayed to inform them of what they need to do.</p>

        {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/progress-steps/progress-steps-validation.svg' | url }}" alt="Progress steps component validation" style="--inline-img-max-width: 687px;">
        {%- endcall %}

        <h4>Completion</h4>
        <p>At any time before a task is completed, a user <strong>is able</strong> to return to any previous steps. When all data in the final step is submitted, a user <strong>is not able</strong> to go back to review or change anything.</p>

        <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
        {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/progress-steps/progress-steps-completion.svg' | url }}" alt="Progress steps component completion" style="--inline-img-max-width: 702px;">
        {%- endcall %}
        </div>

        <p class="footnote" style="margin-top:-3rem; letter-spacing: 0.2px;">When a user reaches the <em>Finished</em> state, they cannot go back to any previous steps without starting over again</p>

    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

        <p>When a user navigates through steps, each step should present content relevant to the step text label. For example, if a user is viewing a text label that says <em>Choose trial</em>, they should be presented with the opportunity to choose a trial from a list. Displaying relevant content and being clear about where a user is in the process will make them feel in control and encourage them to finish the task.</p>

